<item>
            <title>[LU-20085] dir aliases lead to dcache problems</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20085</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;ll_splice_alias() tries to eliminate lustre inode aliases with the same parent and the same name, while dir aliases with different names / parents are allowed. The latter breaks &lt;br/&gt;
dcache locking rules and may lead to locking the same object twice by the Linux VFS code.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="96989">LU-20085</key>
